03:12.158 --> 03:13.796
News of the Week, this is Charlie.

03:15.662 --> 03:17.164
I wonder why she's here.

03:17.330 --> 03:19.606
She's the publisher.
She doesn't need a reason.

03:19.766 --> 03:23.680
Oh, I read an article that despite being
one of the richest people in the country...

03:23.836 --> 03:27.682
...Mrs. Burkhart still enjoys
making her own clothes.

03:27.840 --> 03:31.151
I guarantee you she didn't make
those snakeskin shoes she walked in on.

03:31.311 --> 03:33.621
They look like they cost
at least $50.

03:33.780 --> 03:35.350
$50?

03:35.515 --> 03:38.325
The Burkhart family made their fortune
from Kentucky bourbon.

03:38.484 --> 03:42.364
As the story goes, a giant oak tree fell
on Bea's great great grandfather's house.

03:42.522 --> 03:45.264
He made 40 oak barrels
using that tree...

03:45.425 --> 03:47.632
...and used them for
his first batch of bourbon.

03:47.794 --> 03:49.467
It's now called
Storm Tree bourbon...

03:49.629 --> 03:52.439
...and it's one of the most
sought after in the world.

03:52.665 --> 03:53.700
Hm.

03:54.601 --> 03:57.912
The Burkhart family is a client
of my father's financial firm.

03:58.171 --> 04:00.014
- Oh.
- There it is.

04:01.474 --> 04:04.148
Oh, Naomi, you have a run
in your stockings.

04:04.310 --> 04:06.381
I have an extra pair
of L'eggs in my desk.

04:06.546 --> 04:08.219
Let me get them for you.

04:08.381 --> 04:09.860
Thank you.

04:13.052 --> 04:16.192
Heh, heh, heh.
I tell people when Daddy died...

04:16.356 --> 04:20.827
...he had so much bourbon in his blood,
they didn't have to embalm him.

04:22.495 --> 04:24.031
Thank you.

04:24.297 --> 04:27.073
Just a second and I will join you.

04:27.400 --> 04:28.504
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

04:28.668 --> 04:29.908
Bottoms up.

04:34.274 --> 04:36.083
Mm, wow!

04:36.442 --> 04:39.218
- That is good stuff, strong, strong stuff.
- Mm-hm.

04:39.379 --> 04:41.655
That'll drive you
to put a lampshade on your head.

04:46.552 --> 04:48.088
Well...

04:48.821 --> 04:51.062
...now that we have had
our frivolities...

04:51.224 --> 04:54.398
...let's get down to boring old business.

04:58.364 --> 05:00.435
Gentlemen, for most of my life...

05:00.600 --> 05:03.206
...although my father was
a rich bastard--

05:06.172 --> 05:09.016
I was a failure
at everything I ever did.

05:09.242 --> 05:11.381
I failed at arithmetic...

05:11.544 --> 05:14.150
...I failed at three marriages...

05:14.314 --> 05:17.193
...and I can't get a seed to flower
to save my life.

05:18.518 --> 05:22.796
But despite my failures,
people always remembered me.

05:22.955 --> 05:25.458
Because you were
the daughter of a rich bastard?

05:29.095 --> 05:30.972
Well, that helped.

05:31.130 --> 05:33.371
That has always helped, yes.

05:33.533 --> 05:36.571
Uh, but no.

05:36.903 --> 05:38.974
People remembered me
because I was different.

05:39.405 --> 05:43.649
I said things that
people didn't expect a lady to say...

05:43.810 --> 05:46.256
...I wore things that made
people turn their heads...

05:46.412 --> 05:49.791
...and I did things that, uh...

05:50.083 --> 05:52.654
...well, I usually blamed
on the bourbon.

05:54.187 --> 05:58.363
But I am concerned
that my daddy's magazine...

05:58.524 --> 06:00.902
...is not memorable.

06:01.060 --> 06:02.164
It's not interesting.

06:04.630 --> 06:07.702
There's nothing in our magazine
that I can't read somewhere else...

06:07.867 --> 06:09.847
...and to add insult to injury...

06:10.002 --> 06:12.448
<i>...Time</i> Magazine is kicking our butt.

06:12.605 --> 06:15.211
<i>- We're kicking Newsweek's butt.
- Look,</i> I <i>agree, Bea...</i>

06:15.375 --> 06:16.854
...but the news is the news.

06:17.009 --> 06:18.818
We're gonna be covering
the same story.

06:19.178 --> 06:23.183
Our goal is to tell it
better than anybody else.

06:23.349 --> 06:26.421
- To go deeper inside--
- We won't beat Time at their game.

06:26.586 --> 06:28.122
But the game is changing.

06:28.287 --> 06:31.097
And I can assure you,
we are looking to the future.

06:31.991 --> 06:33.800
And what is it that you see?

06:33.960 --> 06:38.136
Well, before long, Time is gonna be
the old people's magazine.

06:38.297 --> 06:42.006
Meanwhile, there are three million
23-year-old Americans out there.

06:42.168 --> 06:45.240
Their parents read Time Magazine,
which means they're not going to.

06:45.405 --> 06:49.012
They're looking for something different.
I want News of the Week to be that.

06:49.175 --> 06:52.679
So that by the time they're 25,
we're their go-to magazine.

06:52.845 --> 06:54.483
We're the voice that they trust.

06:54.647 --> 06:56.684
- That they can turn to.
- Hm.

06:58.551 --> 07:00.394
How are you going to do that?

07:00.553 --> 07:03.693
- We're working on several initiatives--
- How's he gonna do it, Wick?

07:05.558 --> 07:08.505
Well, we're gonna write about
the things they care about.

07:08.661 --> 07:09.935
Mm-hm.

07:10.329 --> 07:12.366
Civil rights. The draft.

07:14.333 --> 07:17.143
The back of the book stuff,
you know, the arts...

07:17.303 --> 07:18.714
...and rock musicians.

07:18.871 --> 07:21.147
Rolling Stone is less than two years old.

07:21.307 --> 07:23.651
It's got a fraction
of the subscribers Time does...

07:23.810 --> 07:26.450
...and yet the young people
can't stop talking about it.

07:26.612 --> 07:28.614
Jann Wanner,
he is not afraid to take risks.

07:28.781 --> 07:31.421
That is exactly what we need to do.

07:32.151 --> 07:34.495
You are saying that
we're going to lose readers?

07:34.954 --> 07:37.901
Well, you can't win
new readers without--

07:41.360 --> 07:42.896
We may lose some.

07:50.303 --> 07:51.680
Hm.

07:52.371 --> 07:54.044
Yeah, Tuesday.

08:00.379 --> 08:01.380
Robinson.

08:03.082 --> 08:04.823
Rhodes.

08:06.919 --> 08:08.899
You left this
in my apartment a while back.

08:09.055 --> 08:10.534
Thought you might want it.

08:10.690 --> 08:11.896
Need it.

08:12.258 --> 08:14.397
Are you trying to drive a point home?

08:14.560 --> 08:17.541
You will not be sleeping over
at my apartment anymore.

08:18.097 --> 08:20.077
I got it.

08:23.035 --> 08:24.878
We gonna be able to work together?

08:26.572 --> 08:28.108
Yes.

08:28.975 --> 08:30.648
Of course.

08:42.722 --> 08:44.201
Jane.

08:44.991 --> 08:46.231
Finn needs you.

08:54.934 --> 08:57.608
- Bea, you remember Jane.
- Of course.

08:57.770 --> 09:01.684
I knew Jane when she had
braces on her teeth...

09:01.841 --> 09:04.082
...and Gordy Hollander
had a full head of hair.

09:04.243 --> 09:06.086
It is so nice to see you,
Mrs. Burkhart.

09:06.245 --> 09:08.350
Jane was an
excellent recommendation of yours.

09:08.514 --> 09:10.994
She's kind of our head researcher
around here.

09:11.450 --> 09:14.329
Jane, maybe you can give Bea
a tour of the place before lunch.

09:14.987 --> 09:17.160
Well, that would be nice.
It's been a while.

09:17.323 --> 09:19.929
I'd love to revisit how
the sausages are made here.

09:20.226 --> 09:25.403
Well, I would love to show you
around the sausage factory. Heh. Um...

09:25.831 --> 09:27.833
- May I carry this for you?
Oh.

09:28.801 --> 09:30.212
Thank you.

09:41.647 --> 09:44.719
Bill Shawn from New Yorker called
to say he only found two typos...

09:44.884 --> 09:46.420
...in last week's issue.

09:46.586 --> 09:47.894
Son of a bitch.

09:48.054 --> 09:49.897
Inside joke.

09:52.358 --> 09:54.736
- Angie.
- Yes?

09:55.561 --> 09:56.801
Is that a hand?

10:05.037 --> 10:06.038
Yes.

10:06.205 --> 10:07.240
Yes, it is.

10:08.541 --> 10:09.815
It's my daughter.

10:10.176 --> 10:11.951
She woke up too sick
to go to school...

10:12.111 --> 10:14.819
...and my husband's on a
construction site for three weeks.

10:15.114 --> 10:16.991
My neighbor who
watches her in a pinch...

10:17.149 --> 10:20.153
...is at the hospital
having a baby of her own.

10:20.319 --> 10:23.357
I understand how terrible the timing is
with Mrs. Burkhart here--

10:23.522 --> 10:26.002
Angie, I didn't know
you had a daughter.

10:35.601 --> 10:37.342
Hi. What's your name?

10:38.537 --> 10:40.073
Vera.

10:44.310 --> 10:46.551
I hope you feel better soon.

10:50.049 --> 10:52.461
Put her in my office, she can lay down.
Comfy couch.

10:52.618 --> 10:54.689
- What about--
- It's better, it's private.

10:54.854 --> 10:56.458
Are you sure?

10:57.857 --> 11:00.929
